This paper discusses security, privacy, and access control in Information-Centric Networking (ICN), which is a networking paradigm that replaces the host-centric networking paradigm. The paper focuses on the security and privacy concerns in ICN and explores access control enforcement mechanisms. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). However, since the paper also discusses security threats and privacy risks, it could also belong to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, since the paper discusses access control enforcement mechanisms, it could belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.CY (Computers and Society).
